    "text_preview": "Q: How does the author view the interplay between rationality and emotion?"
  },
  {
    "id": 84,
    "properties": {
      "text": "A: The author seems to acknowledge the tension between rational thought and emotion/desire. Point 7 contrasts Buddha's emphasis on intentions with Nietzsche's view that the results of actions matter more than intentions, using a personal example of a painful breakup despite good intentions. This suggests the author sees value in both reasoned analysis and emotional drives."
    },
